<class module="baja" runtimeProfile="rt" qualifiedName="javax.baja.user.UserMonitor" name="UserMonitor" packageName="javax.baja.user" public="true" final="true">
<description>
Detects and fires User Events on User related Components.&#xa; &lt;p&gt;&#xa; Primarily this is used by the UserService and UserPrototypes&#xa; Components. Since both components require events to be fired, it&#xa; makes sense for them to share the same code.&#xa; &lt;p&gt;&#xa; In order to use this class, a Component with a Topic named&#xa; &lt;code&gt;userEvent&lt;/code&gt; which fires &lt;code&gt;<see ref="javax.baja.user.BUserEvent">BUserEvent</see>&lt;/code&gt; must be passed in.&#xa; The specified Component must also forward all events to&#xa; the &lt;code&gt;<see ref="javax.baja.user.UserMonitor#fw(int, java.lang.Object, java.lang.Object, java.lang.Object, java.lang.Object)">#fw(int, Object, Object, Object, Object)</see>&lt;/code&gt; method.
</description>
